					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=64111#64111" class="postlink">This</a> is the code I use to reset the scroll mid-frame to any location I want, it works great.
<br />
<br />Keep in mind that using a status bar together with 4-way scrolling can be tricky, because the status bar limits how much you can scroll vertically. SMB3 for example has a maximum level height of 2 name tables minus the status bar. Crystalis uses IRQs to "skip" over the status bar, preventing it from being displayed in the middle of the game screen. But the simplest solution is to use single screen mirroring, because you dedicate one of the name tables to the gameplay and the other to the status bar, and they'll never overlap. I don't think the MMC3 supports single screen mirroring though.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

