				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Cool, I didn't know about that. The <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/INES_Mapper_118" class="postlink">wiki page</a> is very poorly written though, full of English mistakes even. It took me forever to understand what "This board rely on the fact that the MMC3 ignores A13 and page name table adress with 1k/2k banks like it does to bankswitch CHR." meant, which I'm guessing means that "the MMC3 doesn't make a distinction between pattern table accesses and name table accesses, so it still selects CHR pages when addresses above $1FFF are read".
<br />
<br />Being limited to 128KB or CHR-ROM is a bad side effect, although you can gain some of the lost space back by duplicating tiles that can be used in both name tables and separating the ones that are always used in the same name table.
<br />
<br />EDIT: I modified the wiki page a bit.</div>

					
							<br /><br />
