					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Thanks for all the info!  @tokumaru: that definitely was the problem.  I changed it to write $0360 rather than $2360, and it worked perfectly.  Explains why it was offset by the amount that it was.  I guess $2006 behaves differently depending on whether or not it's currently rendering the frame.  
<br />
<br />I was trying to figure out how Crystalis and SMB3 handled its mid-frame scrolling changes, but couldn't quite follow it.  The example you posted helped out a lot.  One thing I still don't quite understand is why it seems like you're writing the y-scroll to $2005 first, then the x-scroll, before the final write to $2006.  Loopy's doc and my own tests during vblank indicated that should be reversed.  However, it does seem to work with y-scroll first when changing it mid-frame.</div>

